08/05/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- The EU envoy for the Montenegrin independence referendum, Miroslav Lajcak, was due to arrive in Belgrade on Monday (8 May), the first stop on a two-day visit to Serbia-Montenegro. He is scheduled to arrive in Podgorica on Tuesday. Lajcak plans to meet with political leaders and international officials in the two capitals to discuss the 21 May referendum process and ties between Serbia and Montenegro after the poll. Afterwards, he will return to Brussels to brief officials Wednesday. (Tanjug, RTS - 07/05/06)
